\title{Smash sums of [cpos](dt-001D)}
##{A \oplus B = \Set{ (t,x) \in A + B \mid x \neq \bot } \cup \Set{ \bot_{A\oplus B} }} 
\p{The [ordering](dm-0000) and [lubs](dt-0017) are, \em{mutatis mutandis}, as with the non-strict \ref{dt-0031}. This operator is called a \em{smash sum} because the two #{\bot} values from #{A} and #{B} are "smashed" into one #{\bot} value.}
